| Feature           | Encryption at Rest               | Encryption in Transit        |
| ----------------- | -------------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| Purpose           | Protect stored data              | Protect moving data          |
| Examples          | Disk encryption, Blob encryption | HTTPS, TLS, VPN              |
| Threats Prevented | Theft of storage media           | Interception during transfer |
| Azure Tools       | Storage Service Encryption       | SSL/TLS, VPN Gateway         |

For example, Azure Storage protects files at rest while HTTPS protects downloads.

A real-life use case is securing enterprise customer data.

This comparison helps clarify data protection stages.
